title: Compiler Error - Unstable Fingerprints in mir_built.

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

body:
### Code The codebase is getting larger, so its hard to provide a minimal verifiable snapshot, but the below code is what I believe to be the relevant sections. Interestingly after playing with the bug, it only ever popped up on the `entity_type("type")` in the builder. Other parameters showed no apparent issues. ```Rust // ApiEndpoint.rs #[derive(Debug, Builder, Clone)] #[builder(setter(strip_option))] pub struct ApiEndpoint { /// Dataset ID #[builder(default, setter(into))] dataset: Option, #[builder(default, setter(into))] limit: Option, /// Created at date, used for filtering by entities created after a specific date #[builder(default)] created_at: Option>, /// Filter by entity type #[builder(default, setter(into))] entity_type: Option, #[builder(default)] tag: Option, } impl ApiEndpoint { pub fn builder() -> ApiEndpointBuilder { ApiEndpointBuilder::default() } } impl<'a> Endpoint for ApiEndpoint { //..// fn parameters(&self) -> QueryParams { let mut params = QueryParams::default(); params .push_opt("limit", self.limit.as_ref()) .push_opt("filter[datasets]", self.dataset.as_ref()) .push_opt("filter[>created_at]", self.created_at) .push_opt("filter[type]", self.entity_type.as_ref()) .push_opt("filter[tags]", self.tag.as_ref()); params } } // endpoint.rs pub trait Endpoint { /// HTTP Method to use for the endpoint fn method(&self) -> Method; /// Endpoint Path fn endpoint(&self) -> Cow<'static, str>; /// Endpoint Query parameters fn parameters(&self) -> QueryParams { QueryParams::default() } /// Body for endpoints that take body parameters. fn body(&self) -> Result)>, crate::Error> { Ok(None) } } // main.rs let entity_query = EntititesEndpoint::builder() .limit("5") .entity_type("type") .build() .unwrap() .query(&tip_client) .unwrap(); ``` ### Meta `rustc --version
